<div class="br2 mv4 center">
  <%= form_for @changeset, @action, fn f -> %>
    <div class="form-group">
      <%= label f, "Total hours sleep:", class: "f5 b db mb2" %>
      <%= select f, :hours_slept, Healthlocker.ComponentView.get_options("hours_slept"),
        class: "pa3 input-reset bn hl-bg-grey w-100 " <>
        Healthlocker.ComponentView.highlight_errors(@changeset, :hours_slept) %>
      <span class="hl-pink"><%= error_tag f, :hours_slept %></span>
    </div>

    <div class="form-group">
      <%= label f, :wake_count, class: "f5 b db mb2 mt4" do %>
        Times I woke up:
      <% end %>
      <%= select f, :wake_count, Healthlocker.ComponentView.get_options("wake_count"),
        class: "pa3 input-reset bn hl-bg-grey w-100 " <>
        Healthlocker.ComponentView.highlight_errors(@changeset, :wake_count) %>
      <span class="hl-pink"><%= error_tag f, :wake_count%></span>
    </div>

    <div class="form-group">
      <%= label f, "Notes:", class: "f5 b db mb2 mt4" %>
      <p class="i">What affected your sleep? Did you have nightmares or terrors? Did you do
        something to try to get a better sleep?</p>
      <%= textarea f, :notes, class: "pa3 input-reset bn hl-bg-grey w-100 " <>
      Healthlocker.ComponentView.highlight_errors(@changeset, :notes) %>
      <span class="hl-pink"><%= error_tag f, :notes %></span>
    </div>

    <div class="mt4 tr">
      <%= submit_primary "Save" %>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <div class="hl-bg-grey pa3 mt4 br2">
    <h2>Sleep tips</h2>
    <p>Good sleep helps promote both mental and physical wellbeing. Here are some ideas to try.</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Ensure you go outside in natural daylight every day and try
      regular exercise</strong>This can regulate your internal body clock and
      help you concentrate, sleep, look and feel better.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Avoid daytime napping even if you have not slept well the night
      before</strong>If you have to have a nap, limit it to 20 minutes and
      avoid napping after 5pm.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Avoid caffeine, nicotine and alcohol 4 hours before bed and avoid
      late meals or snacking</strong>These can all be stimulating for your
      body and mind.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Avoid using your phone, iPad or laptop an hour before going to
      bed, and avoid using them in bed. Remove digital distractions like TV
      from your bedroom.</strong>The backlight on devices suppresses melatonin
      - the hormone that helps you sleep. If you do need to use them change
      the display settings to reduce the brightness (blue light exposure).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Take a warm bath or shower at least an hour before bedtime</strong>
      The rise and fall in body temperature supports the release of sleep
      enhancing hormone melatonin.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Do some gentle stretching or
      <%= link_to("progressive muscle relaxation",
      to: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9x3tl81NW3w") %></strong>
      This will encourage your whole body to relax and help you sleep.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Have pen and paper by your bed to jot down worrying thoughts or
      ideas</strong>This may help stop you going over and over them.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>If you canâ€™t sleep within 15 minutes of going to bed -
      stop trying: go to another room or sit in a chair and read a book.
      Return to bed when you feel sleepy again</strong>
      This will strengthen the association of bed with sleep rather
      than being awake.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Try the Mindfulness course at the
      <%= link_to("Recovery College",
      to: "http://www.slamrecoverycollege.co.uk/courses.html") %></strong>
      Mindfulness has been shown to improve our emotional regulation, which
      can help sleep.
    </p>
    <p>
      For more information and tips on sleep visit the
      <%= link_to("Sleep Foundation", to: "https://sleepfoundation.org/") %>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Or explore
      <%= link_to("more tips", to: tip_path(@conn, :index)) %> on Healthlocker.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
